    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "No, its acting correctly, you just passing in scalars, the values need to be lists, otherwise you don't have an index, but have values, just like the error message says.\n\n```\nIn [15]: pd.DataFrame.from_dict(dict([ ['key1', [1]],['key2',[2]] ]), orient='columns')\nOut[15]: \n   key1  key2\n0     1     2\n```\n\nNote that this is equivalent to the more used basic constructor.\n\n```\nIn [19]: DataFrame(dict([ ['key1', [1]],['key2',[2]] ]))\nOut[19]: \n   key1  key2\n0     1     2\n```\n"
  },
